The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of several graph problems, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of linear programming in the algorithms suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The focus on graph problems suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of kernelization suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
